{{Infobox saint | name = Abraham and Onesimus of Kiev Caves | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = Saints | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = Kiev Pechersk Lavra, Kiev | venerated_in = Russian Orthodox Church | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | major_shrine = | feast_day = September 3 for Abraham, October 17 for Onesimus | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | quote = }}
'''Abraham and Onesimus of Kiev''' were monks of [[Kiev]] and lived in 12-13 c.
They, with several others, have a [[feast day]] at the [[Kiev Pechersk Lavra|Kiev Caves monastery]] on the Saturday after September 14.
The others commemorated on that day include: *Alexius of Kiev, *Helladius of Kiev, *Sisoes of Kiev, *Theophilus of Kiev, *John of Kiev (an infant), and *John of Kiev (an adult). [[Kiev Pechersk Lavra]] is an orthodox monastery which was founded by the monk [[Anthony of Kiev|St.Anthony Pechersky]], also known as Antony Pechersky, in 1051 at the caves near Kiev (now is the center of the city). In 12-th century Lavra became the center of spreading of Christianity in [[Kievan Rus'|Ancient Rus']].<ref>[https://russiapedia.rt.com/prominent-russians/religion/st-anthony-of-the-caves-antony-pechersky/ Prominent Russians: St. Anthony of the Caves (Antony Pechersky)] Retrieved on 26 Feb 2018</ref> Abraham and Onesimus were buried at the [[Near Caves]]. The feast day of Abraham, the hermit, is on September 3. The feast day of Onesimus, the hermit, is on October 17.<ref>[http://www.vgd.ru/CEMETRY/kpl.htm/ КИЕВО-ПЕЧЕРСКАЯ ЛАВРА (Kiev Pechersk Lavra)in Russian] Retrieved on 26 Feb 2018</ref>
